              <repository/>\n                            <idno type=\"old\"/>\n                        </altIdentifier>\n                    </msIdentifier>\n                    <msContents>\n                        <textLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin</textLang>\n                    </msContents>\n                    <physDesc>\n                        <objectDesc>\n                            <supportDesc>\n                                <support><p>13 joining fragments of a slab of off-white marble (no veining). Height 62.5 cm; width 47.5 cm; depth 2cm (top left), 2.3cm (top right), c.3 cm (base). Intact left, right and at base, but the upper portion is missing, as is one fragment from within the body of the surviving section. Traces of a line of mortar following a line parallel to the edge of the stone are preserved on the face, suggesting that it was at some point subsequently fixed face inwards to another surface, implying subsequent re-use.</p>\n                                    <material ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\n                                    </material>\n                                    <objectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259\">plaque</objectType>\n                                    <dimensions>\n                                        <height unit=\"cm\">62.5</height>\n                                        <width unit=\"cm\">47.5</width>\n                                        <depth unit=\"cm\">2-3</depth>\n                                    </dimensions>\n                                </support>\n                                <condition/>\n\t\t    </supportDesc>\n                            <layoutDesc>\n                                <layout><p>Remains of three lines of Latin text are preserved, together with guide-lines top and bottom of each line. A further three guide lines are preserved below the last line of the text, but with no traces of letters.</p>\n                                    <rs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled</rs>\n                                \t<damage/>\n\t\t\t</layout>\n                            </layoutDesc>\n                        </objectDesc>\n                        <handDesc>\n                            <handNote><p>The letters decrease from 60mm in line 1, to 42-43 mm in line 2 and 35 mm in line 3. The letters are fairly crudely V-cut, not always maintaining the vertical. V is very broad and irregular; E tall and narrow; R has a very small, closed eye; P a large elongated eye; G is tall and narrow. Serifs are basic, as are the triangular interpuncts which occur at every word division.</p>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">60</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">42-43</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line3\" to=\"line3\">Line 3</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">35</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">not measured</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225\">Halaesa</placeName>\t\t\n                                <offset>near\n                                    <placeName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525099\">Castel di Tusa</placeName>\n                                </offset>\n                            \t<geo>37.99907, 14.26197</geo>\n\t\t</origPlace>\n                            <origDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0201\" notAfter-custom=\"0300\" evidence=\"context\" precision=\"low\">3rd century CE</origDate>\n                        </origin>\n                        <provenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">From the excavations of the agora</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\">On display in the lapidarium on site</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" resp=\"#JP\">2011.06.15</provenance>\n                        <acquisition/>\n                    </history>\n                    \n                </msDesc>\n            </sourceDesc>\n        </fileDesc>\n        <encodingDesc>\n             <p>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines</p>\n             <xi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 <xi:fallback>\n                     <p>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values</p>\n                 </xi:fallback>\n             </xi:include>\n\t  <xi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     <xi:fallback>\n\t       <p>ISicily glyphs authority list</p>\n\t     </xi:fallback>\n\t   </xi:include>\n         </encodingDesc>\n        <profileDesc>\n            <calendarDesc>\n                <calendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    <p>Julian Calendar</p>\n                </calendar>\n            </calendarDesc>\n            <langUsage>\n                <language ident=\"en\">English</language>\n                <language ident=\"it\">Italian</language>\n                <language ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek</language>\n                <language ident=\"la\">Latin</language>\n                <language ident=\"he\">Hebrew</language>\n                <language ident=\"phn\">Phoenician</language>\n                <language ident=\"xpu\">Punic</language>\n                <language ident=\"osc\">Oscan</language>\n                <language ident=\"xly\">Elymian</language>\n                <language ident=\"scx\">Sikel</language>\n                <language ident=\"sxc\">Sikan</language>\n            </langUsage>\n            <textClass>\n                <keywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    <term ana=\"#function.honorific\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html\">honorific</term>\n                </keywords>\n            </textClass>\n        </profileDesc>\n        <revisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            <listChange>\n                <change when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database</change>\n                <change when=\"2019-07-19\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag edited the file based on autopsy and study for 2017 edition</change>\n                <change when=\"2020-09-09\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n            \t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003590_tiled.tif\" height=\"4336px\" width=\"3416px\">\n                <desc>Photo J.Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003590.jpg\" height=\"4336px\" width=\"3416px\">\n                <desc>Photo J.Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003590_copy2_tiled.tif\" height=\"3072px\" width=\"2304px\">\n                <desc>Photo J.Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003590_copy2.jpg\" height=\"3072px\" width=\"2304px\">\n                <desc>Photo J.Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina</desc>\n            </graphic>\n        </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"line\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> ·\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/>Res · <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublica</ex></expan> · <expan><abbr>Hal</abbr><ex>aesinorum</ex></expan> ·\n                   <lb n=\"3\"/><space extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> · <roleName type=\"civic\" subtype=\"decurio\"><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan></roleName> · <space extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    <lb/><space unit=\"line\" quantity=\"3\"/>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\">\n                <listApp><app><note>Text from autopsy and study for edition of 2017</note></app></listApp>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <p>To [--?--] Augustus; the res publica of the people of Halaesa, by decree of the town councillors.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <p>It is reasonable to assume that the full titulature of one of the third-century emperors is lost from the first part of the stone, as exemplified by <ref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003586\">ISic003586</ref>, <ref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003587\">ISic003587</ref>, <ref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003588\">ISic003588</ref>. The use of the formula res publica Halaesinorum is also found in<ref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003587\">ISic003587</ref> (for Traianus Decius), and the presence of D.D. in this text might encourage its restoration at the end of that text. This is not the lower part of <ref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003588\">ISic003588</ref> (to Volusianus) since both the stone and the lettering are different.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Prag and Tigano</author>\n                        <date>2017</date>\n                        <citedRange>no.31</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/MI64NB9L\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002630</ref></bibl>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
